Light grill using Kingsford(r) Charcoal with Sure Fire Grooves(tm). Mix garlic, red pepper and salt; rub onto wings. Pour Ranch dressing into Glad(r) food storage bag; add wings. Shake bag to coat wings. Remove wings from bag; place on aluminum foil, fold into cooking pockets and seal tightly. Place pockets on main grill rack for about an hour and a half. Remove wings from pockets and finish directly on grill over moderate flame. Turn every two minutes until wings develop a crust. Baste wings with KC Masterpiece(r) Original Barbecue Sauce. Serve warm.